cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic textual similarity. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of word embeddings and correlation operators, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of algorithms for natural language understanding. The paper also mentions the use of word embeddings in computer vision tasks, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of kernel methods and reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
